CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 29, 1941, pg. 22, reads: "WASHINGTONIANS PROUDLY BOAST OF MANY BEAUTIES - Beauties in Washington, Pa., are not scarce! Above are a few of the many that could have been snapped while chatting in Lincoln Lunch, Lincoln Street, local meeting place for Washington youths.  Top photo shows, left to right: Miss Ella Mae Lacey and Miss Myrtle Thomas... - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Ella Mae Lacey and Myrtle Thomas seated at table with Coca Cola bottles and cigarettes, with Coca Cola poster with female pilot overhead, Lincoln Lunch Restaurant, Lincoln Street, Washington, Pennsylvania
